<BYLINE>Garaldine Price</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>FAIRFAX, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Garaldine </PERSON> `` Garry'' Price, the widow of longtime <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION> congressman <PERSON> Melvin </PERSON> <PERSON> Price </PERSON>, died Sunday of lung cancer at the age of 66. Mrs. Price and Price, a veteran Democrat lawmaker from <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Louis </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ill. </LOCATION>, married in 1952 while she was a field representative for the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cancer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Society </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Denver </LOCATION>.
