<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Siler </PERSON>, a former <LOCATION> Knoxville </LOCATION> sports editor and author of four books, died Sunday after a long illness at age 78. <PERSON> Siler </PERSON>'s career began in 1931 and included stints with The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Nashville </LOCATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sun </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION>. He was <ORGANIZATION> Knoxville </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News-Sentinel </ORGANIZATION> sports editor from 1957-1979.
