<HEAD>Dolls, Rattles Recalled As Choking Hazards For Children</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Several small dolls and rattles marketed as craft goods are being recalled by their manufacturer because they could pose a choking hazard for children, the <ORGANIZATION> Consumer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Product </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> has announced. The toys are being recalled by <ORGANIZATION> Fibre </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Craft </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Materials </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Niles </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ill. </LOCATION>, which said the products could be returned to the place of purchase for a refund. Recalled rattles include `` Baby Rattle 4684,'' a noisemaking blue ball atop a pink beaded handle; `` Plastic Spoon Decoration 4685,'' a pink, blue or yellow spoon with a painted-on face; `` Plastic Ball Decoration 4686,'' a blue and pink barbell; and `` Clothespin Cake Decoration 4687,'' a noisemaking blue clothespin with a blue painted-on face. The dolls are being recalled because their arms may be pulled off and possibly ingested by a child. They include `` Cupid'' dolls numbers 3004, 3035, 3036, 3057, 3058 and 3220; `` Jill'' doll 3062, `` Beth'' doll 3086, `` Baby'' doll 3087 and `` Strawberry Girl'' doll 3101. More information can be obtained by calling Fibre Craft at 1-312-647-1140 or the <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> at 1-800-638-2772.
