<BYLINE>By CRISPIN Y. CAMPBELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A panel of former and present Cabinet-level health officials agreed that care for <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s poor women and children is inadequate but disagreed on how to improve it. <PERSON> Arthur </PERSON> <PERSON> Fleming </PERSON>, who served from 1958-61 as Secretary of Health, Education and Welfare, the forerunner to today's <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Health </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Human </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION>, said the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> needed a `` universal system of coverage'' to ensure adequate care. <PERSON> Margaret </PERSON> <PERSON> Heckler </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> HHS </ORGANIZATION> secretary from 1983-85, agreed that health care services for the poor needed improvement. But Heckler, the current <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> ambassador to <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION>, said, `` If it is based on the system in <LOCATION> Great </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>, we do n't want that. I've seen it and many people are now asking to go to private physicians.'' <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> has a nationalized health care system. `` That's not what we're talking about,'' <PERSON> Fleming </PERSON> countered. `` <LOCATION> Great </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> has got a government in power that has starved the system.'' The comments were made Monday at a meeting of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> to Prevent Infant Mortality, which is composed of HEW and <ORGANIZATION> HHS </ORGANIZATION> secretaries from the <PERSON> Eisenhower </PERSON> through the <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> administrations. The group was asked to help find ways to make child health a national priority, but it issued no program for action. Sen. <PERSON> Lawton </PERSON> <PERSON> Chiles </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Fla </LOCATION>., chairm