<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 `` A Fish Called Wanda'' lured enough moviegoers last weekend to bag first place in the nation's box office rankings, which was weakened by the Olympics and bad weather. `` Wanda,'' a comedy starring <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Cleese </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jamie </PERSON> <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Curtis </PERSON>, earned $ 2.55 million, according to figures provided by Exhibitor Relations Co. It was the comedy's first time in the top slot after 10 weeks of release. But the overall box-office take was down for the weekend. By comparison, `` Moon Over Parador,'' took in $ 3.2 million for first place the previous weekend. `` Between the Olympics and the ball games, both college and professional, and the normal letdown for this time of year, box office suffered,'' said Exhibitor Relations chief <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Krier </PERSON>. `` Hurricane <PERSON> Gilbert </PERSON> and cold weather in some areas were also factors.'' In second place was `` Die Hard'' with $ 2.54 million, followed by `` Moon Over Parador,'' which sold $ 2.45 million in tickets. `` Nightmare On Elm Street 4: The Dream Master,'' earned $ 2.2 million for fourth place. Disney's `` Who Framed Roger Rabbit'' earned $ 2.08 million, edging `` Betrayed,'' with $ 2.07 million, for fifth and sixth place, respectively. In another close-ranking, `` Young Guns'' drew $ 1.9 million for seventh place, and `` Cocktail'' stirred up $ 1.8 million in ticket sales for eighth spot. Ninth was `` Married To The Mob'' with $ 1.39 million, and the <PERSON> Eddie </PERSON> <PERSON> Murphy </PERSON> comedy `` Coming To <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'' re-entered the top 10 with $ 1.30 million for 10th place. Here are the top movies for the weekend as tallied by Exhibitor Relations, with distributor, weekend gross, number of theater screens, average per screen, total gross and number of weeks in release. 1. `` A Fish Called Wanda,'' <ORGANIZATION> MGM </ORGANIZATION>, $ 2.55 million, 1,207 screens, $ 2