<HEAD>Yellowstone Fire Managers Say Fires May Hold, Humidity Helps In
Calif</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS with four grafs to UPDATE with confirmed evacuations,
increases acreage count on Vacaville fire to 17,000 acres, two
firefighters critically injured; picks up 5th graf pvs, `Fifteen
fires ...'; SUBS grafs 10-11 pvs, `The Miller ...' with two grafs
to conform.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By ELLEN HADDOW</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Strong winds late Monday fanned an arson fire over a containment line and into the <LOCATION> Northern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> town of <LOCATION> Vacaville </LOCATION>, forcing 500 people to flee, but cool, damp weather helped firefighters battle blazes in the Northwest. The sheriff's department ordered the evacuation from home in rural <LOCATION> Vacaville </LOCATION>, but most complied voluntarily, said <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Forestry </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Ferreira </PERSON>. The fire, which has destroyed nine homes and charred more than 17,000 acres of brush, is the larger of two major <LOCATION> Northern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> blazes. The other destroyed six homes as it roared across about 8,000 acres of wildland, brush and timber near <LOCATION> Redding </LOCATION>. At the fire in Redding near <LOCATION> Shasta </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, two men clearing burned timber were seriously injured Monday when a tree fell on them, forestry officials said. Both men, suffering head and back injuries, were hospitalized in critical condition, officials said. Fifteen fires still burning Monday had charred 1.39 million acres in <LOCATION> Wyoming </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Montana </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Oregon </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Idaho </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>, said <PERSON> Arnold </PERSON> <PERSON> Hartigan </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Interagency </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Boise </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Idaho </LOCATION>. In all this season, 69,099 fires have blackened 4,140,000 acres, including about 2 million acres in <LOCATION> Alaska </LOCATION>, he said. The dwindling number of civilian and military firefighters in <ORGANIZ