<FIRST>r p PM-PollMethod     09-20 0942</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Poll Method,950</SECOND>
<HEAD>Poll Methods Are Explained</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Poll-Election Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 This <ORGANIZATION> Media </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> General-Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> poll is based on telephone interviews Sept. 6-14 with 1,125 adults in the continental <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. The phone numbers were selected randomly by computer, and interviews were conducted with the adult who had the most recent birthday. The results were weighted to adjust for variations in the sample. The poll has a three-point margin of error, meaning that if every adult American were asked the same questions, the results theoretically would be within three points of the poll's results, 19 times out of 20. The error margin is larger for subgroups _ four points, for example, for those who said they planned to vote and had decided on a candidate. There are other sources of potential error in polls, including the wording and order of questions. These are the questions and responses in this poll; because of rounding, some totals may exceed 100: 1. Do you plan to vote in this year's presidential election, or not? Yes: 85 percent. No: 12 percent. Do n't Know-No Answer: 2 percent. 2a. -LRB- If yes -RRB- <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> is the Republican nominee for president and <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> is the Democratic nominee. Have you definitely decided which presidential candidate you'll vote for in this year's election, or not Yes: 66. No: 30. DK-NA: 4. 2b. -LRB- If yes -RRB- Which presidential candidate will you definitely vote for in this year's election? <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>: 56. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>: 39. DK-NA: 5. 2c. Are you leaning strongly to vote for one of the presidential candidates, or have n't you made up your mind? Yes: 44. No: 50. DK-NA: 6. 2d. Which presidential candidate are you leaning strongly for in this year's election? <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>: 53. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>: 41. DK-NA: 6. 3. Do you think the outcome of the election _ that is, whether <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> wins or <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> wins _ will have a major impact on your life, or wo n't have much impact on your life? Major: 45. Not much: 45. DK-NA: 10. 4. And do you think whether <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> wins or <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> wins will have a major impact on the future of the country, or wo n't have much impact on the future of the country? Major: 71. Not much: 20. DK-NA: 9. 5. If <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> wins, do you think that as president he will be able to accomplish most of what he says he wants to do? Yes: 36. No: 46. DK-NA: 18. 6. What if <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> wins _ do you think that as president he will be able to accomplish most of what he says he wants to do? Yes: 31. No: 48. DK-NA: 21. 7. Regardless of how you may vote, do you think <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> or <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> will do a better job of ... a. helping more people achieve the <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> dream? <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>: 39. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>: 35. DK-NA: 25. b. reducing the federal budget deficit <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>: 38. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>: 30. DK-NA: 32. c. improving education in <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>: 33. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>: 39. DK-NA: 29. d. maintaining a strong defense <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>: 67. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>: 15. DK-NA: 19. e. helping the poor <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>: 21. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>: 56. DK-NA: 23. f. helping the middle class <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>: 36. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>: 40. DK-NA: 25. g. helping the rich <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>: 67. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>: 10. DK-NA: 25. 8. Do you think that <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> ... a. understands the complicated problems a president has to deal with? Yes: 77. No: 16. DK-NA: 7. b. offers a vision of where he wants to lead the country Yes: 60. No: 25. DK-NA: 15. c. has clear positions on the issues Yes: 52. No: 31. DK-NA: 16. d. cares about people like you Yes: 50. No: 37. DK-NA: 13. g. is a strong leader Yes: 50. No: 34. DK-NA: 16. h. says too many things carelessly, without considering the consequences Yes: 42. No: 41. DK-NA: 17. i. would have good judgment under pressure Yes: 60. No: 23. DK-NA: 17. 9. How about <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>. Do you think that <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> ... a. understands the complicated problems a president has to deal with? Yes: 44. No: 45. DK-NA: 11. b. offers a vision of where he wants to lead the country Yes: 62. No: 25. DK-NA: 13. c. has clear positions on the issues Yes: 47. No: 37. DK-NA: 16. d. cares about people like you Yes: 62. No: 24. DK-NA: 13. g. is a strong leader Yes: 47. No: 32. DK-NA: 21. h. says too many things carelessly, without considering the consequences Yes: 30. No: 51. DK-NA: 19. i. would have good judgment under pressure Yes: 51. No: 21. DK-NA: 29. 10. Do you think it's more likely that taxes would be raised in a <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> administration, or in a <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> administration, or is n't there likely to be any difference when it comes to raising taxes <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>: 11. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>: 38. No Difference: 45. DK-NA: 6. 11. Do you think of <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> as a liberal, moderate or conservative? Liberal: 9. Moderate: 28. Conservative: 50. DK-NA: 14. 12. And do you think of <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> as a liberal, moderate or conservative? Liberal: 41. Moderate: 33. Conservative: 11. DK-NA: 15. 13. Are you better off than you were four years ago? Yes: 59. No: 36. DK-NA: 5. 14. Are you better off than you were eight years ago? Yes: 64. No: 31. DK-NA: 6. 15. In the next few years, do you expect your family's financial situation to get better, or worse, or stay about the same? Better: 55. Worse: 6. Same: 33. DK-NA: 5. 16. Who do you think would be better at managing the federal government _ <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> or <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>: 51. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>: 34. DK-NA: 16.
