wake of the killing has suffered setbacks in its efforts to raise money for a community center, Mrs. <PERSON> Fesi </PERSON> said. A woman who took a public role in forming the group moved after she was harassed. `` We could never prove who did it,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Fesi </PERSON> said. `` They even threatened to bomb her house, so she had to move.'' <PERSON> Bluestine </PERSON> said he understood tensions remained, and his client also moved after the shooting. `` It's a bad situation up there, and from my understanding it's still continuing,'' he said `` There's still a lot of problems with teen-age boys.''
