 on everybody's part, and even new technology to accomplish it,'' <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> said But he said, `` the law wo n't let me go beyond five years.'' <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Abramowitz </PERSON>, a spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> Coalition </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Clean </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION>, said the organization, along with the <ORGANIZATION> Sierra </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Club </ORGANIZATION>, believes that a five-year deadline would force such strict control measures that the public would oppose it. He said the environmental groups hoped for a 12 - to 15-year plan The basin has some of the worst air in the country despite auto emissions standards and controls over industrial polluters.
