`` It did n't have a note attached to it and it had been run over,'' he said. <PERSON> Dunning </PERSON> said many students called their parents Friday. `` It created a panic. At one time, they were calling students to the office five and six at a time ... telling them their parents were there to pick them up,'' he said. Those who left and stayed out Monday were not been punished, <PERSON> Wilson </PERSON> said. But he said funding was affected. In <LOCATION> Kentucky </LOCATION>, schools are funded largely on the basis of average daily attendance. If attendance is low, the average drops, and so does the amount of money the system receives.
