entury type of attitude,'' said <PERSON> Patricia </PERSON> <PERSON> Benedict </PERSON>, executive director of <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Indians </ORGANIZATION> for Development of <LOCATION> Meriden </LOCATION>, the other sponsor. `` Powwows are basically social events,'' <PERSON> Benedict </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Karen </PERSON> <PERSON> Cooper </PERSON>, editorial writer at The Eagle, said Tuesday the powwow also educated people about the Indian culture. `` It's like going to a fair,'' she said. The festival, to be held this weekend, has been moved to <LOCATION> Black </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rock </LOCATION> <LOCATION> State </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Park </LOCATION>. It will include American Indian arts and crafts, singers and dancers, a replica of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> England </LOCATION> bark-covered wigwam, storytelling and cooking demonstrations. Last year's event drew more than 3,000 visitors, with the church receiving a share of the proceeds, <PERSON> Roaix </PERSON> said.
