ing to do.'' <PERSON> Espy </PERSON> said plants in the entry-way had been uprooted and paint dashed on some of the plants. `` Something like this should not be a part of the <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> political process,'' said <PERSON> Coleman </PERSON>, contacted by telephone as he headed to <LOCATION> Belzoni </LOCATION> for a day of campaigning. `` We should talk about the issues and beat each other on top of the head with those.'' `` I ca n't imagine any of my people doing that,'' <PERSON> Coleman </PERSON> said. `` Who knows why someone would do something like this. It may not have had anything to do with politics but no matter why it was done, it was totally wrong and I regret to see it.'' <PERSON> Espy </PERSON>, 34, said he had received threatening calls in the past, `` but you always expect those. There has not been an increase in those calls and this is the first time something like this has happened.'' `` I think most Mississippians would be upset to hear something like this has happened but we all realize there are still some ignorant people running around,'' he said.
