<SECOND>AM-Western Landfills,230</SECOND>
<HEAD>House OKs Transfer of Land for Dumps</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The House on Tuesday passed and sent to the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> a bill aimed at permitting the <ORGANIZATION> Bureau </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Land </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Management </ORGANIZATION> to resume transfers of land to Western municipalities and counties for landfills. The bill, approved on a voice vote with minimal debate, exempts landfills from the requirement in current law that land leased or sold to municipalities revert to the government if used for purposes not spelled out in the deed. This requirement could leave the federal government liable for cleanup of any hazardous waste placed in municipal landfills, the bureau concluded last year in suspending transfers of parcels for landfills. More than 300 communities have acquired landfills this way. The <ORGANIZATION> Interior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> added a requirement to the bill that virgin land be inspected to make sure it contains no hazardous waste, and that towns, cities and counties getting these parcels pledge to follow hazardous waste laws and regulations. But these requirements do not affect existing landfills. Rep. <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Synar </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Okla </LOCATION>., chairman of the environment and natural resources subcommittee of the <ORGANIZATION> Government </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Operations </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, had sought tougher requirements from the <ORGANIZATION> Interior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> His subcommittee reported two years ago that the bureau was ignoring guidelines promulgated by the <ORGANIZATION> Environmental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Protection </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> for landfills under the jurisdiction of federal agencies. `` Let me urge the <ORGANIZATION> BLM </ORGANIZATION> to be responsible'' in moving land to municipal ownership, including leased land, <PERSON> Synar </PERSON> said in a statement on the floor Tuesday.
