<BYLINE>By BILL KACZOR</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PENSACOLA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Three men and a woman, their nude bodies found bound and gagged, were shot to death execution-style Tuesday, apparently in drug-related violence, authorities said. <LOCATION> Escambia </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> Sheriff <PERSON> Vince </PERSON> <PERSON> Seely </PERSON> refused to comment on reports that a woman survived the shootings, which occurred at 1 a.m. at a duplex in the unincorporated community of <LOCATION> Pleasant </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Grove </LOCATION> just west of <LOCATION> Pensacola </LOCATION>, on the <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Panhandle </LOCATION>. But neighbor who did n't want to be identified said her son saw a woman in the middle of the highway, calling for help, just as an ambulance and sheriff's deputies arrived. There were several suspects but no arrests by midafternoon, <PERSON> Seely </PERSON> said. The bodies had not been positively identified. Police agencies across the state were alerted to watch for two cars believed to be heading toward <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION>, possibly traveling together. The notice said the occupants were to be considered armed and dangerous. A third car, a tan <ORGANIZATION> Buick </ORGANIZATION> sedan registered to a 24-year-old woman who lived at the address where the shootings took place, was found at the scene with blood stains on it. <PERSON> Seely </PERSON> said all the victims were in their early 30s and each was shot at least once. `` All of the victims were found nude, hands and feet tied and gagged,'' <PERSON> Seely </PERSON> said. `` All victims were shot in the head with a medium caliber pistol.'' <PERSON> Seely </PERSON> said there was no forced entry, but could not say if the victims knew the attackers. He had no comment on reports that at least one victim also was stabbed. He also would not identify the person who reported the shooting, and declined to say whether drugs or other evidence of narcotics dealing were found at the scene. But authorities said the slayings are believed to be drug-related because they were done execution-style. The neighbor said residents of both units in the duplex where the shooting occurred often went from one to the other. She said they had lived there about a year and kept to themselves. The people in the unit adjacent to where the shooting took place had children, the neighbor said. <PERSON> Seely </PERSON> refused comment on that report as well.
